===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|ls=psc|晶|生|c1=p|c2=p|t1=twinkling stars}}. {{och-l|*晶}} originally referred to this word; a phonetic {{och-l|*生}} was added later ([[Wiktionary:About Chinese/references#J|Ji Xusheng, 2004]]). {{och-l|*晶}} was later simplified into {{och-l|*日}}.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart (2014)}} reconstructs the {{cog|och|-}} as {{m|und|*s-tsʰˤeŋ}}, which can be analysed as a verbal root {{m|und|*tsʰˤeŋ||bright}} with a prefix {{m|und|*s-}}. This reconstruction accounts for the Min initial {{m|und|*tsh-}} and the use of the character to write the word {{och-l|晴|tr=*N-tsʰeŋ}}.

Possibly related to {{och-l|清|clear}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart, 2014}}), in turn from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*(t)s(j)aŋ||clear; pure; clean}}.

Proto-{{w|Kiranti languages|Kiranti}} {{m|und|*saŋ||star}} either develops from a parallel {{cog|sit}} root ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}) or derives from {{cog|sit-pro|*sV-kar||star}} (STEDT).

